        <h2>What is the ELSS Stream?</h2>
        <p>
          The <strong>Entry Level and Semi-Skilled (ELSS)</strong> stream is a unique
          category within BC PNP designed for workers in specific industries where
          B.C. faces labour shortages, even if those jobs are not considered "high
          skilled" (TEER 4 or 5 under the NOC 2021 system).
        </p>
        <p>
          Unlike other streams, you cannot apply to ELSS directly from outside
          Canada. You must be working in B.C. already and have gained at least 9
          months of work experience with your current employer.
        </p>

